MCMC in Computer Vision

Computer vision is everywhere: robots, navigation, ATM, autonomous cars and etc etc

In late 20th century, computers was evolving extremely fast, so expensive calculation was no longer an obstacle for many problems. Plus the popularity of Bayesian methods in that period, which had made essential contributions to the development of MCMC like Gibbs sampling, a lots computational problems and complex applications have been solved. Computer vision is one of the fields that are significantly beneficial from MCMC, resulting a rapid evolution in the past couple decades.

Most of the problems CV are super high dimensional. When solving the MLE, MCMC will be required.
